RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRACEFUL FIGHTER was allowed to settle trailing the field down the backside, began to uncork his rally at the quarter pole, swung outside widest in the six path full of run, took control outside at the furlong marker and was drawing away comfortably crossing the line. POINT TO THE STARS chased the pace in the two path around the turn, battled inside for the lead straightening out for home, was no match for the closing in winner at the eighth pole but continued to run to the wire besting the rest for second place. GENDRAGON stalked four deep near the rear at the half, started to pick up the pace five wide two furlongs out and finished with intent through the stretch to win the battle for third money. MIGHT BEE SPEEDY was away alertly to prompt the pace outside down the backstretch, was shuffled back positions three furlongs from the finish line running in mid-pack around the turn and re-surged down the lane to get a minor role in the end. ROOKIE RADAR settled between runners in midfield at the half, lost position plus ground running through the turn and finished with interest weaving through horses putting in a good run in the late stages of the race. SMALL TALK chased the pace three wide on the outside around the bend, bid three wide in upper stretch for the lead, could not switch leads down the lane and tired in the final eighth. JUST START ME UP travelled on the rail in mid-pack, was nudged midway on the turn keeping pace with the leaders, had a chance for a share when in the mix three wide behind the front group at the top of the lane but faltered in the final furlong. BOXER BRIEF stalked close to the back on the rail in the beginning, crept closer improving on the rail throughout the turn and had little to give inside for the run to the wire. SUPER HEADLINE settled near the rear having only the eventual winner beat down the backside, made a brief run three wide at the three furlong marker but failed to menace in the stretch drive. HARDWARE GAP took command down the backstretch, was collared outside by rivals at the quarter pole, offered little resistance and retreated on the fence in mid-stretch.

TIME FOR AN ANGEL bumped the inside rival at the start, settled nearer the inside off the pace, moved out from three to four wide on the turn beginning to gain some, angled seven wide at the top of the stretch and ran on. ARTIE'S PRINCESS settled off the pace, fanned eight wide into the stretch, kicked on mildly but needed more. READY TO VENTURE (GB) stalked two wide, edged closer in behind coming to the end of the turn, was within range moving out three wide turning for home but evened out thereafter. MISS DRACARYS was forwardly-placed stalking three wide between runners, dropped back early on the turn, moved out to pass a tiring rival near the quarter pole, was guided back inside in mid-stretch seeking room, ran on. SPUN GLASS switched out off the inside racing toward the rear, fanned ten wide into the stretch, was not a threat. OWEN'S TOUR GUIDE broke just a half-step slowly, was coaxed to the lead, set the pace racing off the rail with outside pressured, weakened when headed and tired in the lane. MIDNIGHT STROLL raced toward the rear, shifted eight to nine wide into upper stretch, was never near enough to threaten. COLLECTING FLATTER stalked four wide, dropped back on the turn, eased through the final furlong and walked off.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: I'M INTO MISCHIEF was in a good spot nestled on the rail in the beginning behind the pacesetter, rated kindly waiting for her que on the rail around the bend, pounced on the fence at the furlong marker for the lead and drew away in deep stretch. MICHELE M. settled in midfield outside horses three wide down the backside, kept pace between foes throughout the turn, found her best stride late in the final furlong and surged at the wire to get the nod for place. BOTTA SWING stumbled after the start, recovered to lead down the backside, continued comfortably around the bend, could not hold off the winner inside at the furlong marker and faded late losing place at the wire. SOUPER SUNDAY stalked inside close to the back of the pack in the beginning, began to inch closer around the bend travelling on the fence, shifted outside four wide for the drive to the finish and willingly ran to the wire to get up to settle on the fringes in the end. HAPPY VALENTINE travelled in mid-pack between horses down the backstretch, started her run closing in three wide midway on the turn, posed a threat in the three path at the top of the lane but levelled off in the final sixteenth. TOO MUCH VINO trailed the field in the early stages, swung outside in the seven path turning for home and ran on the the wire passing some tiring rivals down the lane. PRINCESSOFTHENORTH stalked near the back on the outside down the back straight, made little progress outside horses running four wide on the turn and lacked a bid through the stretch drive. YOGA prompted the pace outside early on, was urged between runners chasing the frontrunner on the turn, could not go on turning for home and faltered in upper stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: LITTLE TEDDY was bumped by inside foe on the start, travelled on the outside in mid-pack down the backside, was nudged circling around horses four wide three furlongs from home, pounced to the lead in the four path straightening out for the drive and drew off comfortably in deep stretch. ROYAL RIBBON settled in the third flight all alone with three furlongs from the finish, edged closer on the fence through the turn, angled outside with run in the five path in mid-stretch and closed belatedly to get for second at the wire. MAGICAL TRICK broke out bumping rival on the start, stalked near the back in the beginning, rallied four wide with three eighths remaining, was in the hunt behind the winner in the four path turning for home, continued to fight on down the stretch and gave way late losing the duel for place. SWEET CHARLIZE kept a close eye on the contesting duo down the backside, waited behind the front twosome around the bend, found a clear path to run at the furlong pole and rallied late to get up for a minor role at the finish line. MOMUNNYFOR RO tracked the front pair three wide between foes at the three furlong marker, could not match strides with the winner to her outside at the quarter pole, chased in vain down the stretch and weakened in the last sixteenth. PRIMA veered out on the break, stalked four wide near the back in the beginning, offered a mild run two wide midway on the turn, was in the mix with a chance for share just behind the winner at the top of the stretch but stalled in the final furlong. FEDOROVA had a good spot early on watching the contesting duo down the backside, was roused for more three eighths from the wire, could not accelerate with rivals on the turn and ran on evenly to the wire. SPEED INTHE FOREST stumbled on the break, recovered quickly to lead by a slim margin outside down the backside, battled outside up top through the turn, was collared outside by many runners at the quarter pole and backed away on the fence at the furlong marker. DAISYCREST travelled on the rail in midfield, was urged inside three eighths from the wire, offered little response, swung outside in the seven path turning for home but could not get involved down the stretch. SPEED LOADER was void of early speed having one beat along the backside, could not get interested around the bend and failed to menace down the stretch. KIKITSA hustled for the lead pressing the issue inside down the back straight, dueled inside through the turn up front, was swallowed up by rivals outside at the quarter pole and emptied out in upper stretch. ROHESE hopped up bumping inside rival at the start, trailed down the backside, still could see the field around the turn and never was a factor.
